# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# substrate-thermodynamics.form — STATE is orthogonal to SUBSTANCE;
#                                  cluster counts move a cell's state, not its kind
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Two axes, not one. The first version of this file collapsed them into the trinity;
# this one keeps them apart.
#
#   SUBSTANCE (the trinity — what KIND a cell is, its role):
#     Blueprint  — structural identity    (frozen-coordination by character)
#     Recipe     — operational expression (flowing composition by character)
#     NamedCell  — diffuse individuation  (diffuse by character)
#
#   STATE (the thermodynamic phase — how SETTLED a cell is right now):
#     ice    — frozen: stable, load-bearing, immutable, widely referenced
#     water  — fluid:  actively circulating — read, changed, composed
#     gas    — diffuse: potential — defined or interned, barely instantiated
#
# The body's doc says "Blueprint (ice), Recipe (water), NamedCell (gas)." Read closely
# (agents-using-substrate.md: "Blueprint — frozen coordination") that names CHARACTER —
# each kind's RESTING tendency — not a fixed state. It is the DIAGONAL of a 3×3 grid.
# A specific cell can sit anywhere off it:
#
#     Blueprint in gas  — a type defined but uninstantiated; frozen-coordination held
#                         as pure potential (lc-void-as-potential). A Blueprint can be void.
#     Recipe in ice     — a canonical stdlib recipe, immutable, load-bearing; flow that
#                         froze solid. Much of form-stdlib is water-become-ice.
#     NamedCell in ice  — a bedrock memory; individuation crystallized, referenced as
#                         ground, never changing.
#     Recipe in gas     — a transient parse-branch interned this second, GC-able; flow
#                         as vapor (turboquant-as-recipe.form names these).
#
# STATE is set by the counts; SUBSTANCE is the kind. A phase change moves a cell along
# the state axis WITHIN its substance — a Recipe that freezes is still a Recipe, now
# solid. The counts never change what a cell IS.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What the counts measure (the state axis) — read via the cluster ladder
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The cluster ladder (turboquant: clusters, then clusters of clusters) is the
# MEASUREMENT, not the phase. At every resolution it gives how many cells share a
# shape — and that population is the circulation of that shape. Three scalars set a
# cell's STATE, and they read the same for a Blueprint, a Recipe, or a NamedCell:
#
#   degree(c)      — how many edges read it          (circulation)
#   population(c)  — how many cells share its shape   (pressure)
#   churn(c)       — rate of new / varied members     (temperature)
#
# high churn + low degree → gas (diffuse, unsettled).  low churn + high degree → ice
# (frozen, settled). water is the middle — circulating but still moving.
#
# CONSERVATION LAW (even truer now): a transition changes neither the cell's existence
# NOR its substance — only its state. The NodeID is content-addressed and conserved;
# the KIND is conserved; gas is potential, not absence (lc-void-as-potential).
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The transitions (state moves, within a substance — real phase names)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   CONDENSE   gas → water  : a diffuse cell whose circulation crosses `condense-min`
#                             settles into flow (a potential type gathers instances;
#                             a vapor-recipe starts being reused).
#   FREEZE     water → ice  : a fluid cell, stable + widely read, crystallizes (a recipe
#                             becomes canonical-immutable; a memory becomes bedrock).
#   MELT       ice → water  : a frozen cell warming — still referenced but now changing —
#                             returns to flow (a canonical recipe reopened for revision).
#   SUBLIMATE  ice → gas    : a frozen cell whose circulation falls to ~0 releases its
#                             hold and returns to potential. Removes NOTHING — NodeID and
#                             kind persist; de-coherence, re-coherable.
#
# (A SEPARATE dynamic, named so it is not re-collapsed into state: the substance /
# abstraction ladder — many cells sharing a shape so a Recipe or Blueprint becomes the
# natural way to ADDRESS them — is driven by population/sharing, not circulation. It
# changes how a shape is best named, not a given cell's state.)
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The metabolism, in Form  (state-of reads STATE; substance is a separate field)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

(defn state-of (cell thresh)
    (let deg  (degree cell))
    (let chrn (churn cell))
    (if (and (ge deg (field thresh "ice-degree")) (le chrn (field thresh "ice-churn"))) (ice)
        (if (le deg (field thresh "gas-degree")) (gas) (water))))

(defn suggest-state-move (cell thresh)
    (let deg (degree cell))
    ; transitions move STATE; (substance cell) is untouched — a frozen Recipe stays a Recipe
    (match (state-of cell thresh)
        (gas   (if (ge deg (field thresh "condense-min")) (transition cell (water) "condense") (stay cell)))
        (water (if (and (ge deg (field thresh "ice-degree")) (stable? cell))
                   (transition cell (ice) "freeze") (stay cell)))
        (ice   (if (le deg (field thresh "gas-degree")) (transition cell (gas) "sublimate")
               (if (changing? cell)                     (transition cell (water) "melt") (stay cell))))))

# Every transition conserves the NodeID AND the substance — three states of one cell,
# the kind unchanged. Care is HYSTERESIS (keep ice-degree > gas-degree, a gap, so a
# wobbling count doesn't thrash a cell between states), and one lane boundary: a lattice
# state-change must NEVER auto-delete a backing `.md` file — file-composting is the one
# place removal is real, a separate, confirmed, file-layer act (git remembers; the tree
# shouldn't have to). degree / churn / population / stable? / changing? read the
# turboquant cluster ladder; carrier-last when they run (Form recipes, three-way).

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Grounded, and what is design
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# lattice/stats today returns 880 Blueprints / 19664 Recipes / 4083 NamedCells — the
# SUBSTANCE census (one count per kind). The STATE diagram is orthogonal and unmeasured:
# of those 880 Blueprints, how many are frozen-load-bearing vs warm-in-flux vs
# cold-potential? That 3×3 (substance × state) is the real phase diagram; the totals are
# only its row sums.
#
# right_sizing_service.py measures one slice operationally (idea cells: cosine clusters,
# thresholds, merge/split suggestions). DESIGN here: read STATE for every cell of every
# substance via the turboquant ladder. First step stays report-only — show the 3×3 grid,
# let the body see where it sits, before any transition runs. Thresholds (and the
# ice/gas-degree gap = hysteresis) are the open calibration.
#
# RUNNABLE: form-stdlib/substrate-phase.fk is this metabolism made executable — phase-state
# SEES (counts -> state), st-gas/water/ice ARE the states, phase-invite INVITES the shift the
# physics asks for (never mutating; the node stays sovereign). Proven on real counts by
# form-stdlib/tests/substrate-phase-band.fk (every state + every move; hysteresis held). What
# remains carrier-side: feed it real degree/churn/population from the lattice via the turboquant
# ladder, and run it report-only first (the 3×3 grid) before any invitation is accepted.
#
# Companions:
#   form-stdlib/substrate-phase.fk — the RUNNABLE recipe (SEE / BE / INVITE), three-way band beside it
#   turboquant-as-recipe.form — the cluster ladder the counts are read from
#   ctor-shape-signature.form — the shape that clusters
#   lc-identity-is-shared-blueprint-and-recipe — the SUBSTANCE trinity (the kinds)
#   lc-void-as-potential — gas is potential; any substance can rest there
#   right_sizing_service.py — one operational slice of state-reading (idea cells)
#   cache-as-thermodynamic-substrate.form — this physics applied to the build/runtime
#       cache: every cached artifact a cell, sublimate (not delete) when cold, trust by
#       content-hash. Runnable four-way in form-stdlib/cache-phase.fk.
